## QUALITY FILTER AUTOMATION                                       [BLOCKS pass 2]

- [x] Auto-detect quality_filter at runtime — pipeline.py now checks if
      model file exists on disk before running the stage. No curator.yaml
      edits required between passes. (pipeline.py updated)

- [x] Graceful skip with symlink redirect — when quality_filter is skipped,
      pipeline.py creates stages/quality_filter → stages/heuristic_filter
      symlink so downstream stages find their input correctly. (pipeline.py updated)

- [x] Write curator/scripts/train_quality_classifier.sh
      Weak supervision: top/bottom quartile of heuristic scores → hq/lq labels
      fastText supervised, 10 epochs, bigrams, F1 reported on held-out split

- [x] Add make target: train-quality-classifier

- [x] Add make target: curate-full
      Runs: make curate → make tokenizer → make train-quality-classifier
            → make curate-resume STAGE=quality_filter

- [ ] Update docker-curate to call curate-full instead of curate
      so make docker-curate runs the complete two-pass pipeline automatically


## TOKENIZATION AUTOMATION                                         [DONE]

- [x] Auto-detect tokenizer at runtime — pipeline.py now checks if
      tokenizer_model file exists before running tokenize stage.
      No curator.yaml edits required. (pipeline.py updated)


## TOKENIZER CONFIG CLEANUP                                      [IMPROVEMENT]

- [ ] Remove <PAD>, <UNK>, <BOS>, <EOS> from user_defined_symbols in
      tokenizer/configs/tokenizer.yaml — they duplicate pad_id/unk_id/bos_id/eos_id
      and push chat special tokens from IDs 4–9 to IDs 8–13.
      Requires retraining tokenizer and updating all configs that reference
      specific token IDs (SFT, DPO chat templates).


## CURATION PIPELINE                                             [IMPROVEMENT]

- [ ] Parallelize WARC reading in extract.py — use multiprocessing.Pool
      to read multiple WARCs concurrently before distributing to Dask workers.
      Currently sequential: ~30s per WARC × 20 = ~10min just reading.
      Fix: pool.map(iter_warc_records, warc_files) then flatten into one list.

- [ ] Add Wikipedia EN download + extraction to download-data
      Currently only Common Crawl WARCs are downloaded

- [ ] Add CodeSearchNet download to download-data

- [ ] Add progress bar / ETA to curator pipeline stages
      Dask dashboard exists but requires SSH tunnel — add a simple
      tqdm progress log to pipeline.py for headless runs

- [ ] Add stage output size logging
      After each stage, log: input docs, output docs, % retained
      Useful for tuning filter thresholds


## MAKEFILE                                                      [IMPROVEMENT]

- [ ] Fix _check-data-dirs guard — currently checks for /logs which
      may not exist if logs are redirected to /data/logs
      → Check only /data and /results, drop /logs requirement

- [ ] Add make status target
      Shows: which stages have completed (.complete markers),
      disk usage per stage, latest checkpoint


## DOCKER                                                        [IMPROVEMENT]

- [ ] Add .dockerignore to exclude /data, /results, notebooks, docs
      from build context — speeds up docker build significantly

- [ ] Pin base image by digest instead of tag
      pytorch/pytorch:2.1.2-cuda12.1-cudnn8-runtime is mutable
      → use @sha256:... for reproducible builds


## UPLOAD SCRIPT                                                           [DONE]

- [ ] Fix upload_s3.sh to handle pass 1 state gracefully
      Currently exits with error if /data/curated/tokenized has no .bin files
      (these only exist after pass 2 tokenization stage runs).
      Pass 1 state: tokenizer model exists, curated JSONL exists, no .bin/.idx yet.
      Fix options:
        A. Make .bin check a warning not a hard exit — upload what exists
        B. Add --mode flag: pass1 (upload pii + tokenizer) vs pass2 (upload mmap)
        C. Auto-detect what exists and upload accordingly
      Workaround until fixed:
        aws s3 sync /data/tokenizer s3://bucket/slm/data/tokenizer/
        aws s3 sync /data/curated/stages/pii s3://bucket/slm/data/curated/pii/


